        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 1:27PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 125 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Laingsburg, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Owosso, Durand, Perry, Laingsburg, Corunna, Morrice, Bancroft,
Lennon, Bennington, Vernon, and Shaftsburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall may also occurring with this storm and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
